Let $\gamma:H^1(\Omega)\to H^{\frac{1}{2}}(\partial\Omega)$ be the trace operator of order zero, which is linear continuous
and surjective, $\gamma^*$ denotes the adjoint operator. Moreover, if $\Gamma \subseteq \partial \Omega,$
$p_\Gamma:H^{\frac{1}{2}}(\partial \Omega)\to H^{\frac{1}{2}}(\Gamma)$ defined by
