\begin{definition}
A actuators (suite of actuators) is said to be $\Gamma-$strategic if the system under consideration is
regionally approximately boundary controllable on $\Gamma$  at time $b$.
\end{definition}


Before to show our main result in this part, by  Eq.$(\ref{phi})$, for any $z\in L^2(\Omega),$ we have
